name: Pressure Cooker Onion Soup
directions:
• 2 medium onions, peeled and sliced (220g)
  • 2 Tablespoons of olive oil (30ml)
  • 3 cups of beef broth, warm (720 ml)
  • 2 cloves of garlic, peeled
  • 1 Tablespoon of Madeira (optional)
  • salt and freshly ground black pepper
  • fresh parsley, to garnish


  • Heat the olive oil in a pressure cooker on sauté and add the sliced onions. Cook until they are starting to darken and caramelize.
  • Add the garlic and continue to cook the mixture until very dark and jammy. Do not allow the mixture to burn, but you do want to get a lot of color on the onions.
  • Pour in the warm beef broth and bring to a simmer. Secure the lid of the pressure cooker and cook under full pressure for 30 minutes.
  • Allow the pressure cooker to decompress before safely removing the lid.
  • Season the soup with the Madeira (optional), salt, and freshly ground black pepper. Garnish with fresh parsley.

name: Chocolate Pumpkin Pie
directions:
For Pie Crust:

    • 1 cup almond flour (120g)
    • 1/4 cup flax meal (28g)
    • 1/4 cup coconut flour  (28g) 
    • 1/4 cup water (60ml)


    For Pies:

    • 3 tbsp coconut butter (or pumpkin puree) (45g)
    • 3 tbsp coconut cream (45ml)
    • 3 tbsp ghee (45ml)
    • 3 tbsp cacao powder (18g)
    • 1 tsp pumpkin pie spice (blend of ground cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, cloves)
    • Sweetener of choice


    INSTRUCTIONS:

    For Pie Crust:

    • Preheat oven to 350 F (175 C).
    • Mix together all the ingredients to form a dough. Add additional water if needed to form the dough.
    • To make 4 small pie crusts, divide the dough into 4 pieces and roll each out into a flat circle.  Then press each into a greased mini tart pan.
    • Bake for 10-12 min until slightly browned.


    For Pies:

    • Melt the coconut butter, coconut cream, and ghee together in a bowl (you can melt it in the microwave).  Stir in the cacao powder and spices.
    • Blend well and spread into the pie crusts.
    • Chill in the refrigerator for 1-2 hours for a more solid consistency.
    • Sprinkle a bit of cacao or pumpkin pie spice on top.

    • Servings: 4 Pies

name: Asian Tuna Patties
directions:
• 14 oz tuna, canned, drained (400g)
  • 2 tbsp olive oil, more if needed
  • 2 large eggs
  • 1 shallot, minced
  • 2 cloves garlic, minced
  • 2 tbsp flat leaf parsley, chopped
  • 2 tbsp coconut aminos 
  • 1 tsp fresh ginger, grated
  • 1 tsp toasted sesame seeds
  • 1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes
  • Salt and black pepper, to taste


  • In a large mixing bowl, combine tuna, eggs, shallot, garlic, parsley, coconut aminos, ginger, sesame seeds, red pepper flakes, sea salt and black pepper. Mix until ingredients are well incorporated.
  • Form mixture into 8 equal sized patties. Place the patties in the freezer for about 30 minutes.
  • Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the patties to the pan.
  • Fry the tuna cakes for about 3-4 minutes on each side. Use caution as you are flipping them over as they are very delicate and will crumble apart easily.
  • Servings: 4 
  • Serving size: 2 patties

name: Instant Pot Beef and Broccoli
directions:
• 11oz of beef sirloin, cut into chunks (300g)
  • 1 tbsp of olive oil (15ml) 
  • 1/2 cup of beef broth (120ml) 
  • 1 1/2 tbsp of gluten-free tamari sauce (25ml)
  • 1/2 head of broccoli, cut into florets (225g)
  • 1 tsp of ginger paste
  • 1 tsp of garlic paste
  • pinch erythritol
  • Sesame, to garnish


  • Heat the olive oil in a pressure cooker or (instant pot) and brown the beef chunks. Add the ginger and garlic paste and cook for a few seconds before pouring in the beef broth and tamari. Add the broccoli. Give the mixture a quick stir, then secure the lid of the pressure cooker.
  • Cook for 10 minutes, then allow to decompress before safely removing the lid.
  • Use a slotted spoon to remove the beef and broccoli and set aside to keep warm. Keep the sauce on the heat and allow it to reduce by half. Adjust the seasoning with a pinch of sweetener.
  • Serve up the beef and broccoli and pour over the sauce. Garnish with Sesame.

name: Keto Chicken Puttanesca
directions:
• 6 chicken thighs with skin on (about 750g)
  • 1/4 cup of red wine (or water) (60ml)
  • 1/4 cup of water (60ml)
  • 20 olives , pitted and sliced (60g)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400g)
  • 1 Tablespoon of olive oil
  • 1/2 medium onion , peeled and chopped
  • 2 cloves of garlic, peeled and chopped
  • Freshly ground black pepper, to taste
  • Chopped fresh basil leaves, for garnish
  • table salt


  • Preheat the oven to 355°F (180°C). Season the Chicken thighs with salt on all sides.
  • Heat the olive oil in a pan and brown the Chicken until the skin is golden and crispy. Remove the Chicken from the pan and set aside.
  • Add the onion and garlic to the same pan and cook until partially caramelized. Deglaze the pan with the red wine (or water) and cook until all the wine is evaporated. Add the olives, diced tomatoes, and an additional 1/4 cup (60 ml) of water to the pan. Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
  • Place the Chicken thighs in a baking dish and cover with the hot tomato mixture.
  • Place the baking dish in the oven and bake in the oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through. Season the dish with additional salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste.
  • Garnish the dish with chopped fresh basil and serve.

name: Slow Cooker Brisket Chili
directions:
• 1.5 lbs of beef brisket, deboned (675g)
  • 2 cups beef stock (480ml)
  • 1 can of diced tomatoes (400g)
  • 9 oz mushrooms, sliced (255g)
  • 4 tbsp olive oil (60ml)
  • 1 onion, peeled and finely chopped
  • 2 cloves garlic, peeled and finely chopped
  • 1 green bell pepper, seeds removed and finely chopped
  • 1 Jalapeño pepper, seeds removed and finely chopped (optional)
  • 2 tbsp ground cumin
  • 1 tbsp chili powder
  • Salt and freshly ground black pepper
  • 2 green onions, sliced, to garnish (optional)
  • sliced Jalapeño pepper to garnish (optional)


  • In a large pan, add 2 Tablespoons of olive oil. Brown the brisket on all sides and set aside.
  • Add the other 2 Tablespoons of olive oil to the pan and sauté the onions, garlic, mushrooms, green bell pepper, and Jalapeño pepper. Add in the cumin and chili powder as well.
  • Place the brisket and the sautéed vegetables into a slow cooker. Add in the beef broth and chopped tomatoes. Cover and cook for 6 hours on low, turning the brisket every now and then.
  • Shred the meat in the slow cooker and cook for 1 more hour.
  • Garnish with green onions and sliced Jalapeño pepper
  • Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper and serve over mashed cauliflower or cauliflower rice.

directions:

  • Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper, leaving a little extra on the side to make it easy to pull up and out of the pan when you’re done.

  • Lift the cheese out of the pan with the sides of the parchment paper and place on a cool countertop. (If your cheese is extra droopy, it needs to be cooked longer.)

name: Chia Seeds Breakfast Bars
directions:
• 1 1/2 tbsp of ground chia seeds (17g)
  • 1/2 cup of water (120 ml)
  • 3.5 oz of mixed nuts (100 g)
  • 1.5 oz of mixed seeds (42 g)
  • 10 tbsp of coconut flakes (40 g)
  • 3 tbsp Erythritol (25g)


  • Preheat oven to 280 F (140 C).
  • Mix the ground chia and water together.  Set aside.
  • Blend the nuts in a food processor until coarse, but not a powder.  Combine the nuts, seeds, coconut, and sweetener in a bowl. Stir in the chia egg and mix well.
  • Pour the mixture into a dish lined with parchment paper and press down firmly. Place in the oven for 1 hour 10 minutes, then remove from the oven.
  • Turn the oven up to 320°F (160°C) and slice into 6 bars. Bake for another 5 minutes until golden.
  • Remove and allow to cool. Store in an airtight container.
  • Servings: 6 bars

directions:

name: Instant Pot Chicken Curry
directions:
• 4 chicken thighs with skin on (600 g)
  • 3 tbsp of flaked almonds  (15 g)
  • 1 tbsp of coconut oil  (15 ml)
  • 2 tbsp of Thai red curry paste (32 g) 
  • 1 cup of coconut milk (240 ml) 
  • Chopped fresh cilantro, to garnish
  • Salt


  • Toast the flaked almonds in a hot, dry pan until golden. Remove the almonds from the pan and set aside.
  • Season both sides of the chicken pieces with salt.
  • Heat the coconut oil in a pressure cooker and fry the chicken pieces skin-side down until golden and crispy. Remove the chicken with a slotted spoon and set aside skin-side up.
  • Pour any excess rendered fat from the pressure cooker, if desired. Add the Thai red curry paste and coconut milk to the pressure cooker and use a whisk to combine. Cook the mixture for 1 to 2 minutes to emulsify and thicken slightly.
  • Return the chicken pieces to the pressure cooker (skin-side up) and secure the lid. Cook for 14 to 15 minutes over moderate heat. Allow the pressure cooker to naturally release steam before safely removing the lid.
  • Remove the chicken pieces with a slotted spoon and set aside to keep warm. Reduce the remaining coconut curry sauce over high heat until completely thickened. Season with additional salt, if desired.
  • Pour the curry sauce over the chicken pieces and garnish with the toasted flaked almonds and chopped fresh cilantro.

directions:

name: Marinara Mozzarella Chicken
directions:
• 4 boneless skinless chicken breasts (500g)
  • 1 cup shredded mozzarella
  • 10 ounces crushed tomatoes (300g)
  • 2 tablespoons tomato paste *flavor you prefer
  • 1 fire roasted pepper, chopped
  • 1 tablespoon olive oil
  • 1 onion, chopped
  • 4 cloves garlic, minced

  • Arrange the chicken in the sauce and top each breast with 2-3 tablespoons of mozzarella cheese per breast. Transfer to the oven to broil for 1-2 minutes, or until the cheese in browned and bubbling.

name: Chocolate Swirl Cheesecake
directions:
• 16 oz Cream Cheese (450g)
  • 1 1/4 cup Cream, Fluid, Heavy Whipping (300g)
  • 4 tbsp Butter Blend Stick Unsalted (60g)
  • 3/4 cup Unsweetened Shredded Coconut (60g)
  • 1/2 cup Almond Meal Flour (60g)
  • 3 tbsp Cocoa, Dry Powder, Unsweetened
  • 1/4 cup Sugar Free Chocolate Chips (45g)
  • 1/4 cup Erythritol (30g)
  • 2 tsp Vanilla Extract
  • Liquid Stevia
  • 1 package (1 oz) Gelatins, Dry Powder, Unsweetened 
  • 1/2 cup Water (120ml)
  • 1/4 tsp Salt, Table


  • In a food processor process the coconut, almond meal, cocoa powder, erythritol, salt and butter until crumbly.  Press into an 8-inch spring form pan to cover the bottom and up at least an inch on the sides.  Place in the freezer until ready to fill.
  • Bloom the gelatin by sprinkling onto the 1/2 cup of water.  Allow to sit for one minute then place in the microwave and gently heat for 30 seconds, stir to fully melt the gelain.  Set aside to cool.
  • Beat the softened cream cheese with vanilla, salt and stevia. You will need about 1 tsp of liquid stevia.  Add less, taste and then add more a few drops at a time to test for desired sweetness.  Continue to blend until uniform then blend in the warm gelatin mixture with 1 cup (240g) heavy cream.  Be sure the mixture is uniform and then equally divide into two bowls.
  • Heat 1/4 cup (60g) cream in the microwave for 1 minute or up to 2 until just before it begins to boil. Place chocolate chips into a bowl and pour over and allow to sit for 1-2 minutes then whisk until completely melted.  Add to one of the reserved bowls.
  • Pour the vanilla cheesecake batter into the pan with the crust.  Next pour the chocolate batter in a swirl pattern starting in the center and working outwards over the vanilla batter.
  • Place the cheesecake into the refrigerator and allow to set up for at least 2 hours.

name: Asian Baked Salmon
directions:
• 2 portion Prime Salmon Fillet Farmed Atlantic Salmon, Boneless and Skinless 250g
  • 1/2 heads Cabbage, Chinese (Pak-choi) Raw
  • 1 lemon yields Lemon juice Reconstituted Lemon Juice 
  • 2 tbsp Soy Sauce Made From Soy (Tamari)
  • 6 oz Mushrooms Raw 225g
  • 1/2 tbsp Butter With Salt
  • 1/4 tsp Salt, Table
  • 1/4 tsp Pepper, Black 
  • 1 1/2 tbsp Olive Oil 


  • Preheat oven to 475 ºF - 250c.  Juice lemon into a medium bowl and remove seeds. Add tamari sauce and mix to combine. Set HALF of the marinade aside for step 4.  Pat dry salmon fillets with paper towels and season with a pinch of salt and pepper. Place into the medium bowl with the lemon mixture.  Place in the refrigerator and let marinate for 15 minutes.
  • While the salmon is marinating, slice the bok choy in half lengthwise.  Remove the stems from the shiitake mushrooms and discard stems. Slice the mushrooms into quarters; set aside.
  • Place the butter and 1 tablespoon of olive oil on a sheet tray lined with foil. Place in oven for 2 minutes, until butter melts. -- Place the salmon on the prepared sheet tray and place in the oven.  Bake salmon for 8 to 10 minutes or until desired doneness.  Remove from oven and keep warm for plating.
  • Heat a large non-stick sauté pan over medium-high heat with 2 teaspoons of olive oil.  When the pan is hot add the bok choy and mushrooms and cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until fork tender.
  • Add the remaining tamari mixture to the pan and mix to combine.  Remove from heat and set aside for plating.
  • In the center of two plates, place the bok choy and mushrooms.  Place the salmon over the bok choy and mushrooms.

name: Cappuccino Loaf Cake
directions:
For the Cake:

  • 1/2 cup of ghee, softened at room temperature (125g)
  • 1 cup of plain coconut yogurt (227g)
  • 3 large eggs
  • 1/2 tsp of baking powder
  • 2 1/2 cups of almond flour (300g)
  • 1/2 tsp of baking soda
  • 2/3 cup erythritol 
  • 1 tbsp of powdered monk fruit 
  • 1 1/2 tsp of vanilla extract (8ml) 
  • 2 tsp of espresso instant coffee, mixed with 2 tbsp (30ml) of water

For the Icing:

  • 1/3 cup of coconut cream (113g)
  • 1/2 cup of coconut butter, softened (113g)
  • 1 tsp of espresso instant coffee, mixed with 1 tbsp (15ml) of water
  • 3 tbsp of powdered monk fruit
  • 1 tsp of vanilla extract


INSTRUCTIONS:

  • Preheat the oven to 350ºF (177ºC). Grease an 8×4-inch loaf pan and line with parchment paper. Set aside. 
  • Add ghee, coconut yogurt, eggs, baking powder, almond flour, baking soda, and 2/3 cup of erythritol to a large mixing bowl and whisk together until evenly mixed and smooth.
  • Scoop out 1 1/2 cup of the batter and place in a new bowl. Mix in the coffee. Add the 1 tablespoon of monk fruit. 
  • Transfer the two mixes to the prepared loaf pan and, using a spatula, swirl together to create a marble effect. 
  • Bake for 30-40 minutes, or until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean. Leave the cake to cool in the pan for about 5 minutes, before gently turning onto a wire rack. 
  • Meanwhile, whisk together all icing ingredients in a mixing bowl until creamy and refrigerate until needed. 
  • Spread the icing on top of the cooled cake and keep in the fridge for up to 3 days.
  • Servings: 12 slices. Serving size: 1 slice.

directions:

Ganache

  • Pour over top frozen cheesecakes and enjoy!

name: Keto Buffalo Chicken empanadas
directions:
Empanada Dough

  • 1 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese (180g)
  • 3 oz cream cheese (85g)
  • 1 egg whisked
  • 2 cups almond flour (240g)


Buffalo Chicken Filling

  • 2 cups shredded chicken cooked (240g)
  • 2 tbsp butter melted 
  • 1/3 cup hot sauce (optional) 80ml


INSTRUCTIONS:

  • Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. (220c)
  • In a microwave safe bowl add the mozzarella and cream cheese. Take it to the microwave for one minute, stir. Put in the microwave for another minute and stir well until all combined. 
  • Add in almond flour and egg. Mix to combine well and add any additional almond flour as needed for consistency (until stops sticking to your fingers). Set aside.
  • In a bowl, mix shredded chicken with buffalo sauce and Reserve.
  • Cover a flat surface with plastic wrap or parchment paper. Sprinkle with almond flour. Spray a rolling pin with coconut oil and roll the dough flat. Once you've rolled it flat, about ¼" thick, use a cookie cutter or a cup to cut circle shapes. For excess dough, form into a ball then roll out again and repeat the process until all the dough has been used.
  • Place a spoonful into each circle on one half and then fold the other half over. 
  • When forming the empanadas, make sure to press down firmly on the edges. You can also slightly roll the edges to make sure they're combined well.
  • Lay on a lightly greased cooking sheet and cook at 425 degrees for 8-10 minutes until starting to turn golden brown. Enjoy!

name: Keto Salisbury Steak
directions:
• 1 tbsp coconut oil
  • 1/2 lb ground beef (225g)
  • 1/2 tsp ground mustard
  • 1 tbsp reduced sugar ketchup
  • 1/2 tbsp worcestershire sauce
  • 1 small Egg
  • 1/4 cup pork rinds, finely ground (15g)
  • 1/2 tsp Pink Salt
  • 1/2 tsp black pepper

Gravy:

  • 1/4 medium white onion
  • 1 ounces Baby Bella Mushrooms (30g)
  • 1 cups beef broth (235ml)
  • 1/2 tbsp reduced sugar ketchup
  • 1/2 tbsp worcestershire sauce
  • 1/4 tsp xanthan Gum


          INSTRUCTIONS:

          • Slice the onion and baby bella mushrooms and set aside in a bowl.
          • Heat a large skillet to medium high heat.
          • In a large mixing bowl combine all the ingredients for the patties. Combine using your hand and form into 2 even oval patties
          • Add 1/2 tbsp coconut oil to the hot skillet and add the patties to the skillet. Cook 4-5 minutes on each side, until fully cooked through and crispy on the outside.
          • Remove from the skillet and set on a plate.
          • Reduce the heat to medium-low and Drain off 1/3 of the drippings. Add remaining coconut oil to the skillet (1/2 tbsp) and combine and scrap up the bottom using a spatula. R
          • Add the chopped onions and mushrooms and combine using the spatula. Cook for 3-5 minutes until the onion and mushrooms are tender and cooked down.
          • Add the beef broth, ketchup, and worcestershire sauce and combine.Bring to a boil and reduce for 3-5 minutes. Add the xanthan gum, whisk to combine (ensure to get all the xanthan gum clumps mixed in) and then add the cooked patties back into the gravy mixture. 
          • Cook for an additional 5 minutes.

name: Keto Mexican Pizza
directions:
Topping:

  • 1/2 lb lean ground beef (225g)
  • 1 tbsp coconut oil
  • 1 tbsp taco seasoning
  • 2 slice bacon chopped
  • 1 cup marinara sauce (180g)
  • 1 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese (180g)
  • 5 large black olives sliced
  • 1 small tomato (chopped, optional)


    Instructions
    • In a large mixing bowl, mix almond flour with protein powder then add melted butter, olive oil, eggs and almond milk. When adding almond milk, make sure to add little and mix it well as you add. Knead until you get a mixture that is not sticky. If necessary add a little more almond flour. Let this dough rest for 30 minutes.
    • Stretch the dough on a clean surface and make a round shape. If desired, it can be rectangular or square. Put it in a pizza baking tray. Bake the dough at 250F for about 15-20 minutes (depends on your size and thickness) until edge just starts to turn light golden brown then remove from the oven. 
    • While waiting for the crust to be ready, brown the ground beef with coconut oil and taco seasoning in a hot frying pan for 8-10 minutes until cooked. Drain the liquid if necessary. Set aside.
    • Once the crust is ready, spread marinara sauce on the crust then add chopped bacon, cooked ground beef, chopped tomato (without seed) and black olive slices. Finally, add cheese on the top. If you wish to, you can add dried oregano.
    • Bake the pizza for about 8-10 minutes at 300F or until cheese is melted.
    • 8 servings (8 pieces).

name: Shrimp and Broccoli Stir Fry
directions:
• 1.5 lb shrimp fresh or frozen, peeled with tails (680g)
  • 1 lb broccoli cut into florets (450g)
  • 2 tablespoons coconut oil
  • 1 small onion sliced thin
  • 4 cloves garlic minced
  • 3 tablespoons ginger minced
  • 1/4 cup coconut aminos (60ml)
  • 10 drops liquid stevia

  • In a large skillet or wok, melt coconut oil over medium-high.  Add onions and cook until translucent. Stir in the garlic and ginger and stir fry until fragrant.

  • Add the coconut aminos and stevia. Then, stir in the shrimp and salt. Cook until shrimp is heated throughout (or turns pink if using uncooked). Serve hot over cauliflower rice.

directions:
• 12 oz Cheddar Cheese 340g
  • 1 1/2 cups Heavy Cream 350g
  • 4 slices Bacon

  • 14.5 oz can Chicken Broth 400ml
  • 1/2 cup (8 fl oz) Water 120ml

  • In a large saucepan over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Remove, reserving drippings, and drain on paper towels. Crumble bacon.

  • Whisk in thickener. Add cream, water, cheese and paprika, stir until cheese is melted.
  • Ladle soup into four heated soup bowls. Garnish with crumbled bacon.

name: Mocha Ice Cream
directions:
• 2 1/2 cups Heavy Cream (600ml)
  • 1 cup Sucralose (130g)
  • 6 large Egg, Yolk Raw, Fresh
  • 1 tbsp Gelatins, Dry Powder, Unsweetened
  • 1 cup Tap Water (240ml)
  • 1/2 cup Cocoa, Dry Powder, Unsweetened (55g)
  • 4 tsps Rounded Coffee ,Instant Powder, Decaffeinated
  • 1 tsp Vanilla Extract
  • 1/2 tsp Salt


  • Sprinkle gelatin over water and let soften, about 5 minutes.
  • In a medium bowl, whisk yolks and sugar substitute to combine.
  • In a medium pot, mix cream, gelatin mixture, cocoa powder and coffee. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until cocoa and coffee granules have dissolved and mixture has begun to simmer.
  • Slowly pour 1 cup of hot cocoa mixture over egg yolk mixture, whisking constantly. Pour mixture back into pot. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and salt. Chill mixture 4 hours.
  • Transfer the mixture to a freezer container (like a 9x5 in (23x13 cm) loaf pan) and smooth the top with a spatula. Line the surface with a piece of parchment or wax paper to keep ice crystals from forming. (You can use an ice cream maker if you have one.)
  • Freeze for 5-6 hours, until firm. Stir the ice cream during the freezing process, every 30 minutes for the first 2 hours and every 60-90 minutes for 2-3 hours after. (Ice cream will get hard in the freezer after longer periods. Let it soften on the counter for 10-30 minutes before serving, and use a wet ice cream scoop to serve.)

directions:
• 3/4 lb Asparagus 340g
  • 1 cup Leeks, fresh chopped
  • 1 tsp Garlic
  • 1/3 cup Cream, Fluid, Heavy Whipping 80g
  • 14.5 oz Soup, Beef Broth Bouillon And Consomme Canned 400ml
  • 2 tbsp Butter Unsalted Stick


  • Melt butter in a large pot over medium-high heat. Clean leeks and dice the white and some of the green top.  Chop asparagus into 1-2 inch pieces.  Add leeks to the pan and sauté for 3 minutes. Add asparagus and cook 1 minute more. Add garlic and sauté for 30 more seconds.
  • Add broth to pot and bring to a boil.
  • Lower heat, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, until asparagus is tender.
  • Mix in cream, and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Blend soup in a food processor or blender until smooth.
  • Return to pot to heat through before serving (if necessary). Season with additional salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste.

  • Discard toothpicks and serve immediately.  Each serving is 2 wraps.

name: Peanut Butter Protein Truffles
directions:
• 6 tbsp Peanut Butter, Smooth Style 180g
  • 1/2 cup Coconut Cream, Canned 120g
  • 1 Scoop  Chocolate Whey protein 30g
  • 1 dash Salt, Table 
  • 8 tbsp Sugar Free Chocolate Chip 50g
  • 1/3 tbsp Vegetable Oil, Coconut 


  • In a mixing bowl, mix the peanut butter, coconut cream, and salt together until well combined, you may need to warm them in the microwave to be able to completely incorporate. 
  • Add the protein powder and mix until all the powder is worked in, and a smooth texture develops. The mixture will be slightly oily.
  • Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Make 15 balls by scooping one tablespoon of the peanut butter mixture and using your hands to form into a ball. Place the balls on the parchment paper lined baking sheet and put into the freezer to cool for 30 minutes.
  • While the balls are cooling, melt the chocolate chips and coconut oil together, stirring until fully melted and uniform texture. Keep warm until the balls are well cooled.
  • Remove the balls from the freezer and, one at a time, roll in the melted chocolate to coat. Place each coated truffle back on the parchment paper and refrigerate until the chocolate has hardened, about 10 minutes.

name: Cauliflower Mac & Cheese
directions:
• 1 large head of cauliflower
  • 1 cup heavy whipping cream (240ml)
  • 3 ounces cream cheese (90g)
  • 1 cup cheddar cheese (120g)
  • 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese (60g)
  • 1/4 cup parmesan cheese (30g)
  • 1 teaspoon onion powder
  • 1 teaspoon garlic powder
  • salt and pepper to taste


  • Preheat the oven to 375 degrees and then prepare a baking dish with cooking spray. 
  • Cut a head of cauliflower into florets. Steam or boil for approximately 5 minutes, until they are crisp and tender. Strain the cauliflower and put it in your baking dish and then add salt and pepper to taste.
  • In a skillet over medium-high heat, add heavy whipping cream and bring it to a simmering boil. Whisk in garlic powder, onion powder, and salt and pepper to taste.
  • Add cream cheese and stir until smooth, and then add cheddar cheese. Sprinkle in mozzarella cheese and stir until cheese sauce thickens.
  • Pour the cheese sauce over the top of the cauliflower in the baking dish and stir to coat the cauliflower in the cheese sauce. Sprinkle parmesan cheese over the top of the cauliflower.
  • Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the mixture is browned on top and bubbly. For a more browned appearance, cook in broiler for the lat few minutes.

name: Cheesy Zucchini Bake
directions:
• 1 1/2 pounds zucchini (680g)
  • 1 small white onion
  • 2 medium garlic cloves, pressed
  • 1/2 cup olive oil (120ml)
  • 4 eggs
  • 1 cup almond flour (120g)
  • 4 teaspoons baking powder
  • 1/2 cup Parmesan, Shredded Cheese (60g)
  • 1/2 cup Mozzarella, Shredded Cheese (60g)
  • 1/2 teaspoon salt
  • 1/2 teaspoon pepper
  • 1/4 teaspoon dried basil
  • butter to grease your pan
  • fresh parsley for garnish


  • Preheat your oven to 375f (190c).
  • Rinse your zucchini and slice off the tip and root ends. Pat your zucchini dry with a paper towel. Leave the skin on.
  • Slice your zucchini into 1/8-inch rounds. Place your zucchini slices into a large mixing bowl.
  • Peel and finely chop your onion and add it to your bowl.
  • Add your pressed garlic.
  • In a liquid measuring cup, add your oil, then beat in your eggs with a fork. Pour the egg/oil mixture into your bowl with the zucchini.
  • Add your flour, baking powder, Parmesan, mozzarella, salt, pepper and basil to your bowl.
  • Use a wooden spoon to carefully mix everything until combined well. Try to separate any zucchini slices that are stuck together.
  • Transfer your zucchini mixture to your greased pan and smooth it out evenly. Bake uncovered for 55-60 minutes, or until the entire top is browned (but not burned).
  • Garnish with parsley and serve.

name: Keto Cinnamon Rolls
directions:
• 1 1/2 cups shredded mozzarella (175g)
  • 3/4 cup almond flour (90g)
  • 2 tbsp cream cheese
  • 1 egg
  • 1/2 tsp baking powder

Filling:

  • 2 tbsp water
  • 2 tbsp Sukrin
  • 2 tsp cinnamon

 Frosting:

  • 2 tbsp cream cheese
  • 1 tbsp greek yoghurt
  • 2 drops vanilla stevia


INSTRUCTIONS:

  • Pre-heat oven to 180 Celsius/360 Fahrenheit.
  • Melt the mozzarella and cream cheese in a non-stick pot over a low heat or in a microwave (1 1/2 minutes, stirring half way through). Take off the stove and/or make sure the cheese is melted, but not bubbling.
  • Stir in the egg.
  • Now add the almond flour and baking powder. Start to combine using a fork, then use your hands to make a ball of smooth dough. 
  • Divide the dough into 4 balls
  • Form long rolls, then flatten out with your hands. Make the dough as thin as you can.
  • Prepare your cinnamon filling: boil water, then stir in the sweetener and cinnamon.
  • Spread the cinnamon paste over the flattened dough rolls.
  • Roll each into a bun and cut sideways in half.
  • Now you have 8 buns which you place on a non-stick baking sheet or in a pie dish.
  • Bake for ca 20 minutes.
  • While the rolls are in the oven, prepare the frosting: Mix cream cheese, yoghurt and stevia.
  • Spread over the warm rolls and serve

directions:
• 2 lb Beef, Top Sirloin Separable Lean Only, Trimmed To 1/4" Fat,(900g)
  • 1 teaspoons Salt

name: Keto paneer chicken
directions:
• 1 lb bone-in chicken thighs (450g)
  • 7 oz  paneer packet (200g)
  • 1 cup water (240ml)
  • 1 cup crushed tomatoes 
  • ½ cup heavy whipping cream (120ml)
  • 4 tablespoons butter
  • 1 tablespoon olive oil
  • 2 teaspoons coconut oil
  • 1 ½ teaspoons garlic paste
  • 1 ½ teaspoons ginger paste
  • 1 teaspoon salt
  • 1 teaspoon black pepper
  • ½ teaspoon paprika
  • ½ teaspoon red chili powder
  • 5 sprigs cilantro



  • Preheat oven to 375°F (190c)
  • Get the chicken thighs out and rub them down with olive oil. Add salt and pepper to taste.
  •  Put the chicken on a cookie sheet and let them roast for 25 minutes.
  •  Cut the paneer into small pieces and set aside for later.
  •  Heat up a pan to medium heat and add the butter and coconut oil. Let the butter start to brown.
  •  When the butter starts to brown, add ginger and garlic paste. Saute for 2 minutes.
  •  Add the crushed tomato.
  •  Add the coriander powder, paprika, red chili powder and the salt. Mix well and let it simmer until the oil is starting to show at the top.
  • Gently mix the paneer into the sauce.
  •  Pour in the water and let it simmer for 5 minutes.
  •  Turn the heat to medium low and add cream. Stir to mix.
  •  Allow it to simmer until it comes to a boil again.
  •  About this time, your chicken will be ready. Take it out and separate it from the bone 
  •  Add chicken to the sauce and mix well.
  •  Allow to simmer for at least 5 more minutes
  •  Garnish with Cilantro and serve hot.

name: Keto Fish Nuggets
directions:
• 1/2 cup of finely ground pork rinds (30g)
  • 1/2 cup of parmesan cheese (30g)
  • salt/pepper/cayenne/garlic powder
  • 1 egg
  • 1 tbsp heavy cream
  • 3 frozen vacuum sealed tilapia fillets
  • a few tbsp of oil 



  • Thaw the fish by letting the still vacuumed fillets sit in a bowl of hot water for a few minutes.
  • Use a food processor or mortar and pestle to finely ground the pork rinds into a powder.
  • In one bowl, thoroughly mix the pork rind powder with the parmesan and whatever spices you've chosen.
  • In a second bowl, whisk the egg and heavy cream.
  • Cut the thawed fish into nuggets about 1 inch squares .
  • Heat a skillet to medium-high heat, then add enough oil to coat the entire surface to a depth of 1/4 inch.
  • Thoroughly coat the fish in the egg mixture on all sides, then thoroughly coat it in the pork rind/cheese mixture and toss it in the oil.
  • Fry until it’s golden brown, (about 2-3 minutes) flipping half way through.

directions:

name: Keto Tortillas
directions:
• 1/2 cup shredded asiago (60g)
  • 3 tablespoons coconut flour
  • 1 large egg 



  • Heat a dry cast iron skillet over medium heat.
  • Mix the shredded cheese and coconut flour in a glass bowl.
  • Microwave for one minute or until cheese is softened.
  • Stir well to combine and slightly cool the cheese mix. Add in the egg and mix until a dough forms.
  • Separate the dough into 4 equal size balls.
  • One at a time, flatten the ball between parchment paper until 1/8 inch thick.
  • Place the tortillas on the hot cast iron skillet and heat 2-3 minutes a side until lightly browned.
  • Take it from the heat and let them cool a little.

name: Crispy Chipotle Chicken Thighs
directions:
• 12 ounces boneless chicken thighs (350g)
  • 3 cups fresh baby spinach (100g)
  • ½ teaspoon chipotle chili powder
  • ¼ teaspoon garlic powder
  • ¼ teaspoon onion powder
  • ¼ teaspoon ground coriander
  • ¼ teaspoon smoked paprika
  • Salt and pepper
  • 1 tablespoon olive oil


  • Combine the chipotle chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, coriander, and smoked paprika in a small bowl.
  • Pound the chicken thighs out flat then season with salt and pepper on both sides.
  • Cut the chicken thighs in half and heat the oil in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
  • Add the chicken thighs skin-side-down to the skillet and sprinkle with the spice mixture.
  • Cook the chicken thighs for 8 minutes then flip and cook on the other side for 3 to 5 minutes.
  • During the last 3 minutes, add the spinach to the skillet and cook until wilted.
  • Erve the crispy chicken thighs on a bed of wilted spinach.

directions:
• 2 chicken breasts, sliced (400g)
  • 18 white button mushrooms, sliced (180g)
  • 3/4 cup of warm chicken broth (180ml)
  • 3 tbsp of coconut cream (45ml)
  • 2 tbsp of olive oil (30ml)

directions:

  • 1 cup of mushrooms, sliced (150g)
  • 1 cup of hot chicken broth (240ml)
  • 1 tbsp of olive oil 
  • 3 tbsp of Marsala, optional

  • Place the chicken breasts between two sheets of baking parchment and use a cook’s mallet to flatten them until they are of even thickness.

  • Taste the sauce to check for seasoning and garnish with chopped parsley

name: Keto Cookie Butter
directions:
• 1 3/4 cup almond flour (210g)
  • 1/2 cup coconut flour (56g)
  • 1/4 cup erythritol (48g)
  • 1/2 cup ghee (120ml)
  • 1 large egg, at room temperature
  • 3/4 cup coconut oil, melted (180ml)
  • 1 tbsp ground cinnamon (6g) 
  • 1 1/2 tsp ground ginger
  • 1/2 tsp allspice
  • 1/2 tsp baking powder
  • Dash of salt


  • Preheat oven to 325 F (160 C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
  • Mix all the ingredients together except for the coconut oil and mix well to form a dough.
  • Divide the dough into small even pieces. Flatten the pieces on the baking sheet.
  • Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until lightly browned on the top but still soft to the touch.
  • Allow the cookies to cool slightly.
  • Grab your high-speed blender and add about half of the melted coconut oil to the blender. Toss all of the cookies on top, and then add the remaining oil on top.
  • Blend on medium-high speed until the mixture forms a butter.
  • Pour the butter into a glass container and store in the fridge for up to 10 days (just bring to room temperature before serving).

name: Bolognaise and Zoodles
directions:
• 12.5 oz zoodles or 3 zucchinis, spiralized (360g)
  • 1 lb of ground beef (450g)
  • 3/4 can of diced tomatoes (300g)
  • 1 cup of beef broth (240ml)
  • 1 tbsp of olive oil (15ml)
  • 1 medium onion, peeled and finely chopped (110g)
  • 2 garlic cloves, peeled and minced
  • 1/4 teaspoon of dried oregano
  • salt and freshly ground black pepper
  • parsley, to serve


  • Heat the olive oil in a large pan and add the onions and garlic. Cook over moderate heat until softened. Add the ground beef and increase the heat, cooking the beef until no longer pink.
  • Add the tomatoes, beef broth, and dried oregano. Reduce the heat to moderate and cook partially covered for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking. Once all the liquid has cooked down, remove the pan from the heat and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.
  • Prepare the zoodles by placing a dash of water into a large pan over high heat. Add the zoodles and cooking until all the moisture in the pan has evaporated and the zucchinis have cooked through (this won’t take longer than a minute or two.) Season with salt.
  • Serve the bolognaise with the cooked zoodles and garnish with parsley.

name: Keto Coq Au Vin
directions:
• 1 tbsp of olive oil (15ml)
  • 8 chicken drumsticks (1000g), with skin on
  • 10–12 baby onions (660g), peeled and left whole
  • 18 white button mushrooms, halved (180g)
  • 3 garlic cloves, peeled and finely chopped
  • 1 tbsp Brandy (optional)
  • 1/2 cup of dry red wine (125ml) 
  • 1 tbsp of tomato paste
  • 1 cup of chicken stock (240ml)
  • fresh thyme, leaves picked
  • 1 sprig rosemary
  • 1 bay leaf
  • parsley for granish


  • Heat the oil in a large, non-stick pan and fry the chicken drumsticks until the skins are golden and crispy. Remove the chicken using tongs and set aside.
  • Add the onions and mushrooms to the pan and cook in the rendered fat until caramelized. Add the garlic towards the end of frying the onions and cook for one minute.
  • Deglaze the pan with the red wine and optional Brandy. Cook until there is no moisture left in the pan.
  • Whisk the tomato paste into the chicken broth, then pour into the pan. Add the thyme, rosemary, and bay leaf to the pan.
  • As this point, return the chicken drumsticks to the pan. Bring the mixture to a low simmer, then cover the pan with a well-fitting lid. Cook for 30-35 minutes on the stove to ensure the chicken cooks through. Use (clean) tongs to carefully remove the chicken pieces from the pan and set aside to keep warm.
  • Remove the lid and heat the sauce over moderate-high heat until it reduces by two-thirds.
  • Return the chicken to the pan, covering with the sauce. Garnish with the parsley and Serve warm with your favorite side.

name: British Scones with Blueberry Jam
directions:
For the scones:

  • 1/2 cup of almond flour (60g)
  • 1 tsp of baking powder
  • 10 tbsp of coconut flour (70 g)
  • 1 tsp of baking soda
  • 3 tbsp of Erythritol (36g)
  • 2 medium eggs
  • 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract

For the accompaniments:

  • 3 1/2 oz of fresh blueberries (100g)
  • 1/3 cup of coconut cream (80ml) 
  • 1 tbsp (12g) of powdered Erythritol


      INSTRUCTIONS:

      1. Preheat the oven to 340°F (170°C).
      1. Combine the coconut flour, almond flour, baking powder, baking soda and Erythritol in a bowl. In a separate bowl, whisk to combine the eggs with the vanilla extract. Pour the egg mixture into the flour and mix well to combine.
      1. Form 4 balls from the dough and place them on a rimmed baking tray lined with parchment paper. Flatten the tops of the dough slightly with the palm of your hand.
      1. Place the baking tray in the oven and bake for 12 to 15 minutes, rotating the tray halfway through. Remove the baking tray from the oven and set aside to cool.
      1. Meanwhile, to make the blueberry jam, place the blueberries in a small saucepan and heat gently while using a potato masher or fork to mash them. Continue to cook until all excess liquid has evaporated. Set aside to cool completely.
      1. To make the sweet coconut cream, simply combine the coconut cream and powdered Erythritol.
      1. Serve the scones with the blueberry jam and sweet coconut cream, if desired.


      Servings: 4

      Serving Size: 1 scone with 1/4 of the blueberry jam and sweet coconut cream

name: Sunshine Breakfast Casserole
directions:
• 8 oz of Italian sausage (225g)
  • 1/2 head of broccoli (225g), chopped into small florets 
  • 1/2 medium red bell pepper (60g), diced
  • 8 medium eggs, whisked
  • 1 Tablespoon of turmeric (6g)
  • 1/3 cup of water (80ml) 
  • Olive oil, for cooking
  • Salt and pepper, to taste


  • Preheat the oven to 350 F (180 C). Grease a casserole dish with olive oil and set aside.
  • Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add the Italian sausage to the pan and cook for 5 minutes, using a wood spoon to break into smaller pieces.
  • Add the broccoli and bell pepper to the pan  and cook for an additional 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
  • Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the eggs, water, and turmeric.
  • Spread the sausage mixture evenly in a casserole dish. Pour over the egg mixture over the vegetables, using a spoon to gently combine the mixture.
  • Place the casserole dish in the oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden and the eggs are cooked through.
  • Remove the dish from the oven and serve immediately.

name: Keto Zucchini Bread
directions:
• 1 cup grated zucchini (150g)
  • ½ cup chopped walnuts (30g)
  • 3 large eggs
  • ½ cup olive oil (120ml)
  • 1 tsp vanilla extract
  • 2 1/2 cups almond flour (300g)
  • ½ tsp salt
  • 1 1/2 tsp baking powder
  • 1 1/2 cups erythritol (180g)
  • ½ tsp nutmeg
  • 1 tsp ground cinnamon
  • ¼ tsp ground ginger


  1. Preheat oven to 350°F (175c). Whisk together the eggs, oil, and vanilla extract. Set to the side.
  1. In another bowl, mix together the almond flour, erythritol, salt, baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon, and ginger. Set to the side.
  1. Using a cheesecloth or paper towel, take the zucchini and squeeze out the excess water.
  1. Then, whisk the zucchini into the bowl with the eggs.
  1. Slowly add the dry ingredients into the egg mixture using a hand mixer until fully blended.
  1. Lightly spray a 9x5 loaf pan, and spoon in the zucchini bread mixture.
  1. Then, spoon in the chopped walnuts on top of the zucchini bread. Press walnuts into the batter using a spatula.
  1. Bake for 60-70 minutes at 350°F or until the walnuts on top look browned.

name: Simple Tofu Scramble
directions:
• 1 package (12.3-oz) firm tofu (340g)
  • 2 ounces vegan cheddar cheese (56g)
  • 1 cup baby spinach
  • 1  small tomatoes
  • 3 tbsp avocado oil
  • 2 tbsp diced yellow onion
  • 1 1/2 tbsp nutritional yeast
  • 1/2 tsp garlic powder
  • 1/2 tsp turmeric
  • 1/2 tsp salt


  • Wrap your block of tofu in a few layers of paper towel, or a clean cloth towel, and gently squeeze some of the water out. Set aside.
  • In a skillet on medium heat, sauté the chopped onion in 1/3 of the avocado oil until the onion is soft and translucent.
  • Place the block of tofu in the skillet and crumble using a potato masher or fork until it’s the consistency of scrambled egg.
  • Drizzle with the rest of the oil and sprinkle with the dry seasoning then gently stir to coat.
  • Cook the tofu over medium heat, stirring and folding occasionally until most of the liquid has evaporated.
  • Fold in the baby spinach, diced tomato and cheese and cook for an additional minute or until the spinach wilts and the cheese is melted.
  • Serve hot and store leftovers in the refrigerator for up to three days!

directions:
• 2 cups almond flour (240g) 
  • 2 Tablespoons apple cider vinegar (30ml)
  • 1/4 cup coconut flour  (28g)
  • 3 Tablespoons unsweetened cacao powder (18g)

  • 1 egg, whisked
  • 1 teaspoon baking soda
  • 1 teaspoon baking powder

  • Preheat oven to 350 F (175 C).
  • Puree the beet and add in the vinegar and ghee.
  • Mix all the cookie ingredients together in a bowl until a soft dough forms.  Place into the fridge for 30 minutes.
  • Form small balls from the dough (use a Tablespoon scoop).  Press into a round cookie and place onto a parchment paper lined baking tray.  The cookies spread so make sure to leave enough room between the cookies.

  • Bake for 20 minutes.  Let cool before enjoying.
  • Yield: 24 cookies (8 servings)

name: Keto Fish Tacos
directions:
For The Fish:

  • 14 oz of white fish fillets, skin removed and deboned (400g)
  • 2 tbsp of coconut flour (14g)
  • 2 tbsp of olive oil, divided (30ml)
  • Salt

For The Soft Tacos:

  • 1 cup of coconut flour (112g)
  • 2 tbsp of psyllium husk powder (32g)
  • 2/3 cup of lukewarm water (135g)
  • 1 tbsp of olive oil (15ml) 
  • 4 teaspoons of olive oil (20ml), additional for cooking
  • 1/2 tsp of baking soda
  • 1 medium egg
  • Salt, to taste

To Assemble:

  • 1 lime, zest and juice
  • 4 Tablespoons of Keto Mayonnaise (60ml) (recipe)
  • Soft lettuce leaves
  • 1/4 medium red onion, thinly sliced (28g)
  • Small handful of chopped fresh cilantro


To Make The Fish:

  • Cut the fish into smaller pieces and scatter over the coconut flour on all sides. Season with salt.
  • Heat 2 Tablespoons (30 ml) of olive oil in a clean pan and fry the fish pieces until golden and cooked through.
  • Drain on a plate lined with a paper towel.

To Make The Soft Taco Shells:

  • Combine the coconut flour, psyllium husk powder, baking powder, and salt, to taste, in a large bowl.
  • In a separate bowl, whisk to combine the egg, lukewarm water and 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of olive oil.Add the liquid mixture to the flour mixture and use a wooden spoon to combine well.
  • Divide the mixture into 4 equal-sized portions. Roll each one into a ball and flatten between two sheets of baking parchment paper – to the approximate size of a small plate. 
  • Heat 1 teaspoon (5 ml) of olive oil in a nonstick frying pan and gently place the dough into the pan. Cook for several minutes, flipping halfway through the cooking time. Set aside and repeat the process until you have 4 soft taco shells.

To Assemble The Tacos:

  • Make a mayonnaise by finely grating the zest of one lime into the Keto Mayonnaise. Combine well and spread 1 Tablespoon (15 ml) of the Keto Mayonnaise over each taco shell.
  • Hold each taco shell in your hand and fill with the soft lettuce leaves and fried fish. Top the tacos with the sliced red onions and chopped fresh cilantro. Squeeze over a little lime juice, if desired.

name: Keto Tiramisu Jars
directions:
• 1/4 cup of erythritol sweetener  (50g)
  • 1/4 cup ghee, melted and cooled slightly (60ml)
  • 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla extract 
  • 1/2 teaspoon of baking powder
  • 1/2 cup of almond flour  (60g)
  • 1/4 cup of coconut flour (28g)
  • 1/4 teaspoon of salt
  • 2 small eggs
  • 1/2 cup of strong coffee, cooled (120ml)
  • 1 cans of coconut milk, chilled overnight (400ml)
  • 1/2 cup of powdered sweetener (100g) 
  • 1/4 oz of 100% dark chocolate (7g)
  • 1 Tablespoons of cacao powder (6g)


  • Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line an 8×8-in pan with parchment paper.
  • Beat the eggs and sweetener together with a hand mixer or stand mixer until light and fluffy.  
  • Add the melted ghee and vanilla extract, then beat again.
  • Mix the flours, baking powder, and salt in another bowl. Fold in the egg mixture.
  • Pour dough into the pan and spread out evenly. Bake for 15-20 minutes until lightly golden and a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
  • Once cooked, remove from the oven and allow to cool completely.
  • Meanwhile, prepare the coffee and set it aside to cool.
  • Spoon out the solid coconut cream from the top of the chilled cans of coconut milk and add to a bowl. Beat with a mixer until light and fluffy – it will take a few minutes.
  • Beat in the powdered sweetener gradually and add to taste.
  • To assemble the jars, use a cookie cutter to cut out rounds of sponge. Dip the sponge rounds in the coffee for a few seconds and allow it to absorb some of the fluid. Place a round at the bottom of each jar. 
  • Spoon a layer of coconut cream in to each jar followed by a sprinkle of cacao powder. 
  • Repeat until you have used up the sponge and cream – you should have between 2-3 layers in each jar depending on the size of your jars. For the final layer, grate some dark chocolate on the top.
  • Add the lids to the jars and place in the fridge to chill for at least 2 hours before serving.

name: Keto Raspberry Cookies
directions:
• 1 1/4 cups of almond flour (150g)
  • 1/4 cup of coconut flour (30g)
  • 1 teaspoon of baking powder
  • 1/2 cup of erythritol (65g)
  • 4 oz of raspberries, chopped small (125g)
  • 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract (5ml)
  • 1 Tablespoon of ghee (15ml)
  • 1 medium egg


  • Preheat the oven to 355°F (180°C).
  • Combine the almond flour, coconut flour, baking powder, and sweetener in a bowl. Tip in the chopped raspberries and mix well to evenly combine. Set aside.
  • Whisk the egg and vanilla together in a small bowl. As long as the ghee isn’t piping hot, drizzle it slowly into the egg, whisking continuously until well combined.
  • Pour the wet mixture into the dry ingredients and mix well. The raspberries will start to color the mixture into a lovely pink.
  • Divide the dough into 10 equal portions. Using the palm of your hands, compress into a ball then flatten into a cookie shape. Place on a tray lined with parchment paper.
  • Bake in the oven for 10-12 minutes, rotating the tray halfway through.
  • Remove and allow to cool completely before serve.

  • Add the tomatoes, chicken broth, and Italian seasoning and bring to a soft boil for approximately 10 minutes.
  • Add the lemon zest and cream and let them cook together for another 10 minutes.

Garnish with parsley and serve

directions:

name: Keto Rice Pudding
directions:
• 1 packet shirataki rice (225g)
  • 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk (120ml)
  • 1 cup heavy whipping cream (240ml)
  • 1 tsp vanilla extract
  • 1 tsp xanthan gum
  • 2 eggs
  • 1/4 cup Erythritol (50g)
  • 1/2 tsp Cinnamon or nutmeg, to taste


  • To prepare the shirataki rice, drain and place in a sauce pan filled with water. Boil for 2-3 minutes, and pour through a fine mesh sieve to drain. Set aside.
  • Place the nut milk, cream and vanilla in a small saucepan and heat over med heat until very hot, but not boiling.
  • Meanwhile, combine egg, erythritol and xanthan gum in a large mixing bowl and whisk well until smooth and well combined.
  • Take the hot milk and add a small amount at a time to the egg , whisking well in-between.
  • Once all of the milk is combined, pour the mixture back into the saucepan and heat again until the custard is thick and creamy. Add the shirataki rice and stir through.
  • Serve with a sprinkle of nutmeg or cinnamon. Can be served warm or cold. Store in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.

directions:

name: Chocolate Nutella Cups
directions:
For Nutella:

  • 1 cup peeled hazelnuts (150g)
  • 1/2 bar 100% dark chocolate (40g)
  • 3 tsp Erythritol
  • 1 tsp cacao powder
  • 1 tsp vanilla extract

Chocolate crust:

  • 1 1/2 bar 100% dark chocolate (120g)


For Nutella:

  • Preheat the oven to 190 °C/ 375 °F. Spread the hazelnuts on a baking tray and roast for 10 minutes until slightly golden. Remove from the oven and allow to fully cool.
  • Meanwhile, melt the chocolate in a water bath. Place the bowl over a pan with boiling water and allow the chocolate to melt whilst occasionally stirring. 
  • Once the nuts have cooled slightly, add to a food processor and blend until smooth. Add the cacao powder, Erythritol, vanilla and blend. Add the melted chocolate and pulse until combined.

For Crust and Cups:

  • Melt the chocolate, place about a teaspoon into the bottom of mini silicone moulds and coat the sides of the mould by swirling round the sides. Place back in the fridge for 10 mins.
  • Add a little Nutella, then fill it with the remaining chocolate.
  • Place the cups in the fridge to set, (about 20 minutes).

name: Keto Yeast Bread
directions:
• 5 large egg whites
  • 3 large egg yolks, divided
  • 2 tbsp apple cider vinegar (30ml)
  • 2 cups warm water, divided (480ml)
  • 1 tbsp yacon syrup (15ml)
  • 1 tbsp active dry yeast (10g)
  • 1 1/4 cup almond flour (150g)
  • 1/2 cup flax meal (75g)
  • 1/2 cup coconut flour (60g)
  • 1/4 cup unflavoured whey protein powder (25g)
  • 6 tbsp whole psyllium husks, powdered (24g)
  • 1 tsp cream of tartar
  • 1/2 tsp baking soda
  • 1 tsp salt


  • Preheat the oven to the lowest setting. Pour 3/4 cup (180 ml) of the warm water into a bowl. Add yacon syrup and stir until fully dissolved. 
  • Sprinkle with active dry yeast. Open the oven for about 1 minute to cool down slightly. Place the bowl in the oven. The light will be enough to keep the bowl warm.
  • Allow to proof for 10 minutes. When ready, the yeast will be frothy and will grow in volume. While the yeast is proofing, line a loaf pan with parchment paper (5 x 8 inch loaf pan.).
  • Once the yeast have proofed, remove the bowl from the warm oven. Meanwhile, place all of the remaining dry ingredients in another bowl and mix to combine.
  • Add the egg whites and two egg yolks into the bowl with the proofed yeast. Add the vinegar and 1 1/4 cup warm water (300ml). Use a hand mixer and process until well combined. Add the dried mixture gradually and process well.
  • Transfer the dough into the lined loaf pan. Spread using a spatula. Place in the oven and let it proof with the oven light on to 60 minutes.
  • Once the dough has proofed, remove from the oven. Preheat the oven to 200 °C/ 390 °F. Whisk the remaining egg yolk with about 2 teaspoons of water. Gently brush on top of the bread.
  • Bake for about 60 minutes. Remove from the oven and let it cool down, slice and serve.

name: No Bake Chocolate Coconut Bars
directions:
Chocolate Base:

  • 1 1/4 cup almond flour (125g)
  • 1 1/2 tbsp cacao powder (8g)
  • 2 tbsp ChocZero syrup (30ml)
  • 4 tbsp coconut oil, at room temperature (60ml)

Coconut Layer:

  • 2 1/2 cups shredded coconut (190g)
  • 1/4 cup Erythritol (40g)
  • 1 tbsp vanilla extract 
  • 3/4 cup coconut cream (200g)
  • 4 tbsp coconut oil (60ml)

Chocolate Coating:

  • 5 oz 100% dark chocolate (140g)
  • 3 tbsp coconut oil (40g)


    To Make the Chocolate Base:

    • Combine the almond flour, Syrup, coconut oil and cacao powder in a bowl and mix well.
    • Line a loaf tray with baking paper, and then pour the mixture in, using wet hands to press down firmly.

    To make Coconut Layer:

    • Add the coconut, erythritol, vanilla, coconut cream and coconut oil into a large bowl and mix well.
    • Scoop onto the chocolate base and press down.

    To make Chocolate Coating:

    • Melt the chocolate with the cocoa over very low heat.
    • Pour over the coconut layer.
    • Refrigerate at least an hour before slicing into bars and serving.
    • Store in the freezer up to six months.

name: Chocolate Swiss Roll
directions:
For Cake:

  • 1/2 cup almond flour (60g)
  • 1/4 cup coconut flour (30g)
  • 1/4 cup cacao powder (22g)
  • 1 tbsp psyllium husk powder (8g)
  • 6 large eggs
  • 1 tsp baking powder
  • 3/4 cup Erythritol (120g)

For Filling & chocolate ganache:

  • 2 cups heavy whipping cream, divided (480ml)
  • 7 oz 100% dark chocolate, grated (200g)
  • 4 tbsp Erythritol (40g)
  • 1/4 cup mascarpone cheese (60g)


  • Preheat oven to  200 °C/ 400 °F. Using hand mixer, beat the eggs and Erythritol until doubled in volume. Gently fold in the dry ingredients.
  • Pour into a greased and lined baking pan. Bake for 12 minutes. Remove from the oven and let stand for 3 minutes.
  • Turn out onto baking paper and very gently roll up along the long side. Wrap the roll in a clean tea towel and leave to completely cool.
  • To make the ganache, place the chopped chocolate into a heatproof bowl. Heat half of the heavy whipping cream (1 cup) in a saucepan until very hot, but not boiling. Pour the cream over the grated chocolate and let stand without stirring for 5 minutes. After 5 minutes, whisk the ganache until smooth and glossy with no lumps. Sit aside to thicken.
  • Whip the remaining heavy whipping cream, mascarpone and Erythritol together until thick. 
  • Unroll the cake. Spread the cream filling all over it evenly and then re-roll it, sitting it seam-side down.
  • Place it in the fridge for half an hour to chill. Carefully ice with ganache before serving.

name: Beef Stroganoff Soup
directions:
• 1.3 lb beef sirloin steaks (600g)
  • 1 lb mushrooms, sliced (450g)
  • 3 tbsp ghee (45g)
  • 2 cloves garlic, minced
  • 1/2 onion, chopped (55g)
  • 3 1/2 cups chicken stock or vegetable stock (840ml)
  • 2 tsp paprika
  • 1 tbsp Dijon mustard 
  • juice from 1 small lemon 
  • 1 cup heavy whipping cream (235g)
  • 1 tsp salt
  • 1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper
  • Chives for garnish


  • Use a sharp knife and slice the steaks into thin pieces. Season with some salt and pepper.
  • Grease a large pan with half of the ghee. Once hot, add the beef slices in a single layer. Quickly fry over a medium-high heat until browned from all sides. Remove the slices from the pan and place in a bowl. Set aside.
  • Grease the pan with the remaining ghee. Place the chopped onion and minced garlic in the pan and cook until lightly browned for about 2-3 minutes. Add the sliced mushrooms and cook for 3-4 more minutes while stirring occasionally.
  • Add Dijon mustard, paprika, and pour in the chicken stock. Add lemon juice and bring to a boil. Cook for 2-3 minutes. 
  • Add the browned beef slices and cream. Garnish with chives and serve.

name: Mexican Cauliflower Rice
directions:
• 1 head of cauliflower, cut into florets (about 700g)
  • 14 oz Canned chopped tomatoes (400g)
  • 7 oz Mexican chorizo, finely cubed (200g)
  • 1/4 cup ghee or butter (60ml)
  • 1/2 small onion (35g)
  • 1 1/2 tbsp tomato puree (23g)
  • 2 garlic cloves, minced
  • 1/4 tsp chipotle flakes
  • 1 cup vegetable stock (240ml)
  • 1/4 tsp salt, or to taste
  • 1/4 tsp black pepper
  • bunch of fresh cilantro (20g)
  • juice of 1 small lime (30ml)


  • Food process the cauliflower until it resemble a rice sized consistency. 
  • Place the ghee in a pan. Add the onions and sauté for 2 minutes on a medium heat until soft. Add the chorizo and fry for a further 5 minutes. 
  • Stir through the garlic. Add the tomato puree, chopped tomatoes, chipotle flakes and season. Simmer on a medium heat for about 5 minutes until the sauce starts to thicken.
  • Add the cauliflower rice and stir until combined. Add the stock and simmer on a medium heat for about 15 minutes until almost all the stock has absorbed.
  • Remove from the heat and stir through the lime juice and fresh cilantro.
  • You can store it in the fridge for up to 4 days.

name: Keto Lemon Bars
directions:
Lemon Curd Layer:

  • 1/2 cup fresh lemon juice (120ml)
  • grated zest of two lemons
  • 1/3 cup Erythritol (70g)
  • 2 large eggs
  • 2 egg yolks
  • 3/4 tsp glucomannan powder

Crust:

  • 2 cups almond flour (230g)
  • 3 tbsp butter, melted (45ml)
  • 4 tbsp almond milk (60ml)
  • 4 tbsp Erythritol (40g)
  • 1/2 tsp xanthan gum

Topping:

  • 1 tbsp powdered Erythritol 


To Make the Crust:

  • Preheat oven to 170 °C/ 340 °F.
  • combine all crust ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
  • Line a tray (8 x 8 in) with baking paper, and then pour the mixture in, pressing down firmly. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until just starting to brown.

To Make the Lemon Curd:

  • Whisk together all of the lemon curd ingredients in a bowl.
  • Pour onto the base while its still hot. Spread across the base, and return to the oven, lowering the temperature to 160 °C/ 320 °F. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until just set in the centre.
  • Allow the pan to cool completely, and then move to the fridge for at least 2 hours before slicing.

Cut it into squares, 16 squares.

Sprinkle with powdered erythritol before serving.

Store in a sealed container in the fridge up to 5 days.

name: Keto Tuna Shakshuka
directions:
• 6 large eggs
  • 2 tbsp ghee or avocado oil (30ml)
  • 1/2 medium onion, chopped (50g)
  • 2 cloves garlic, diced
  • 2 tbsp tomato paste (30g)
  • 1 can tuna, drained (142g, 5oz)
  • 1 tsp turmeric
  • 1/2 tsp ground cumin
  • 1/2 tsp paprika
  • 1/2 cup water (120ml)
  • salt and pepper, to taste
  • 3 tbsp chopped cilantro + 1 tbsp for garnish


  • Grease a large skillet with 2 tablespoons of avocado and sauté onions for about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook for 1 more minute.
  • Add the tomatoes paste. After 1 minute, add tuna and stir well. Add all the spices, salt and pepper, water, and then stir.
  • Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and let it simmer for about 10 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened. Add cilantro chopped and stir.
  • Using a spoon, make 6 wells in the skillet and carefully crack the eggs inside each. Once the egg whites seem to be cooked, cover the skillet to cook the top of the eggs, checking periodically to ensure the yolks don't get overcooked.
  • Remove from the heat and garnish with fresh cilantro.

directions:

  • salt and black pepper to taste
  • 1/4 teaspoon Xanthan gum
  • 1 tablespoon butter


  • Set instant pot to sauté. Add oil to pot and add thighs skin-side down. Cook until golden and crisp. Flip and cook until browned on the other side. Remove chicken from pot.
  • Add onion and garlic to pot and cook until starting to soften, about 1 minute. Add chicken broth, lemon juice, herbs and seasoning. Stir, scraping the browned bits off the bottom of the pot.
  • Place chicken thighs back in the instant pot. Secure lid and set the pressure valve to "sealing". Choose "pressure cook" (or "manual") and "high" for 12 minutes. Naturally release pressure after cooking time is up (just switch off the instant pot and leave it alone until pressure is gone).

directions:
Crust:

  • 1 medium head of cauliflower (550g)
  • 1/2 cup parmesan cheese, shredded (90g)
  • 1/4 cup mozzarella cheese (30g)
  • 1 egg
  • 1/4 teaspoon salt
  • 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
  • 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano

  • 1 1/4 cup mozzarella cheese, shredded (150g)


  • Pre-heat oven to 480F (250C). Cut the cauliflower florets off from the stems.
  • Using a food processor, pulse the cauliflower florets until it resembles small crumbles (similar to pieces of rice).
  • Microwave the riced cauliflower in a microwave safe bowl for 5 minutes.
  • Let the cauliflower cool for a few minutes, then squeeze as much liquid out of it as possible. You can use a kitchen towel or cheesecloth to help with this.
  • Add the egg, parmesan cheese, mozzarella cheese, and spices. Stir together well until combined.
  • Spread the cauliflower mixture onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake for 10-15 minutes until lightly golden brown and slightly crispy on the edges.
  • Top with tomato sauce and mozzarella cheese. Return to the oven for 5-7 minutes. Slice and serve.

directions:

name: Instant Pot Orange Chicken
directions:
For Chicken:

  • 1 lb chicken breast (450g)
  • 2 tbsp olive oil
  • ½ tsp fresh ginger grated
  • ½ tsp garlic minced
  • 1/2 tsp black pepper
  • sea salt to taste
  • sesame seeds, for serving

For orange sauce:

  • ¼ cup chicken broth (60ml)
  • 1 tbsp orange zest
  • 1 tsp orange extract
  • 1 tbsp apple cider vinegar
  • 1 tsp erythritol
  • 1 tbsp coconut aminos
  • 1 tsp xanthan gum + 1 tbsp water, to thicken the sauce


  • Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces. In a bowl, mix all sauce ingredients (except xanthan gum).
  • Turn the “saute” mode on your Instant and let it heat up. Pour in olive oil and wait until hot. Then add garlic and ginger. Cook for 30 seconds.
  • Add chicken pieces, season with salt and pepper, and cook for 3-4 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally. Turn the “saute” mode off.
  • Pour in the sauce and give a good stir. Put the lid on, press “pressure cook” (manual), and cook on high pressure for 5 minutes. Make sure you turn the valve to “sealing.” Once the time is up, do a quick release and take the lid off.
  • Dissolve 1 tsp of xanthan gum in 1 tbsp of water and add this mixture to the instant pot. Turn “saute” mode on again and cook for an additional 5 minutes or until your sauce reaches the desired consistency.
  • Transfer the chicken to the platter. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and serve (You can serve it with cauliflower rice)

name: Instant Pot Mini Cheesecakes
directions:
• 10 oz soft cream cheese (280g)
  • ¼ cup sour cream (58g)
  • 2 tbsp erythritol (30g)
  • ½ tsp vanilla extract 
  • 1 tbsp olive oil for greasing
  • 2 eggs 


  • In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and erythritol until creamy. Add eggs and continue to beat until incorporated. Add sour cream and vanilla extract then beat until combined.
  • Grease small ramekins with olive oil and fill each ramekin with the cheesecake batter.
  • Pour 1 cup water into Instant Pot and place rack that comes with pot inside. Put ramekins on rack.
  • Put the lid on and turn the valve to “sealing.” Press “pressure cook” (manual) and cook at high pressure for 3 minutes.
  • Once the cooking time is completed, let the pressure to release naturally, approximately 12-15 minutes. Once the pin drops, open the lid and remove the ramekins from the pot.
  • Allow the cheesecakes to cool to room temperature then transfer to the fridge to chill for about 3 hours. Top with your favorite berries and serve.

name: Crispy Onion Rings
directions:
• 1 medium onion
  • 2 large eggs
  • 1 tablespoon water
  • 1/4 cup almond flour (30g)
  • 1/2 cup coconut flour (56g)
  • 1 cup parmesan cheese, grated (90g)


  • Pre-heat oven to 425F (220C). Cut the onion into half-inch slices and break it into individual rings.
  • In a food processor, pulse the almond flour and parmesan cheese until a crumby consistency appears. Place in a bowl and set aside.
  • Beat the eggs and water together in a bowl and set aside. Also put the coconut flour in another bowl.
  • With each ring of onion, dip into the coconut flour, then the egg wash, then the parmesan mixture.
  • Repeat the breading process again, starting with the egg wash then coconut flour, then egg wash again, then parmesan mixture.
  • Repeat the double-breading with all onion rings until each onion ring is well coated.
  • Place the double-coated onion rings on a wire rack and bake for 16-18 minutes or until golden brown.

name: Chicken with Creamy Spinach Sauce
directions:
• 1.5 lbs skinless boneless chicken breasts (680g)
  • 1 cup heavy cream (240ml)
  • 3 cups spinach leaves (90g)
  • 2 oz cream cheese, softened (56g)
  • 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese (90g)
  • 2 tablespoons butter
  • 2 tablespoons olive oil
  • 1/3 cup finely diced onion (18g)
  • 3 cloves garlic
  • 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper
  • 1 cup chicken broth (240ml)


  • In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil over medium heat. 
  • Cut the chicken breasts into pieces and season well with salt and pepper. Cook chicken for 3-5 minutes per side. Remove from the skillet and place on a plate.
  • Add the butter, onions, garlic, and crushed red pepper to the skillet and cook for 1-2 minutes.
  • Add the cream, chicken broth and cream cheese. Simmer over medium heat for a couple of minutes, whisking until creamy.
  • Stir in the Parmesan and spinach and simmer until spinach has wilted. The longer you cook the sauce the thicker it will be. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Return chicken to the pan in the sauce until warmed then serve.

name: Curry Coconut Creamed Kale
directions:
• 6 cups chopped kale (400g)
  • 1 cup unsweetened coconut cream (230g)
  • 3 garlic cloves, lightly crushed
  • 1/2 teaspoon curry powder
  • 1 tbsp olive oil
  • 2 tsp ground coriander
  • Pinch cayenne pepper
  • Salt, to taste


  • Bring a pot of salted water to boil and add kale for 3-4 minutes, until it is bright green and wilted.
  • Heat oil in a large skillet over medium. Add garlic and cook, stirring often, until golden brown, about 3 minutes. 
  • Add kale, coconut cream, curry powder, cayenne, ground coriander, salt to the pan.
  • Cover and let simmer for about 13-18 minutes, until greens are tender and mixture looks creamy.

name: Sweetened Condensed Milk
directions:
• 15 oz heavy whipping cream (440g)
  • 2 tbsp butter (30g)
  • 3 oz allulose (85g)
  • 3 oz erythritol (85g)


  • Add all the ingredients in a large, shallow skillet. Over medium-high heat, bring to a boil.
  • Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until condensed by half, stirring every so often to prevent scorching (about 15-20 minutes) color will change to a light golden color. 
  • When ready, remove from the heat and pour into a jar to cool. Let the condensed milk cool completely before putting on the airtight lid. Just note, it thickens up alot after a few hours in the fridge.

name: Grilled Chicken Caprese
directions:
• 1 lb chicken breasts, 4 slices (450g)
  • 4 slices mozzarella (115g)
  • 4 slices tomato
  • 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
  • 1/2 teaspoon onion powder
  • 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning
  • 2 tablespoons basil sliced
  • salt and pepper


  • Preheat grill or grill pan to medium high heat.
  • Season chicken breasts with italian seasoning, garlic and onion powder. Sprinkle with salt and pepper on both sides.
  • Spray the grill with non stick cooking spray and cook the chicken breasts until they are almost fully cooked.
  • Top each chicken breast with a slice of mozzarella. Close the grill and allow it to cook for a few additional minutes to melt.
  • Remove the chicken from the grill and top with tomato and basil.

name: Zucchini Beef Saute
directions:
• 10 oz beef, sliced (300g)
  • 1 zucchini , sliced (300g)
  • 3 cloves of garlic, diced or minced
  • 2 tbsp gluten-free tamari sauce 
  • 2 tbsp Avocado oil to cook with (or olive oil)
  • Salt, to taste
  • Paprika


  • Place 2 tablespoons of avocado oil into a frying pan on high heat.
  • Add the strips of beef into the frying pan and saute for a few minutes on high heat.
  • When the beef is browned, add in the zucchini strips and keep sauteing.
  • When the zucchini is soft, add in the tamari sauce, salt, paprika and garlic.
  • Saute for a few minutes more and serve immediately.
